[normal]My Recommendations
[normal]I recommend that the Joint Committee adopt the proposals within the formal submissions of the following organisations Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance (YDGLA), The Green Lanes Environmental Action Group (GLEAM), The Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG), and The Peak District Green Lanes Alliance (PDGLA), namely that::
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]All Unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATS), and all unsealed Unclassified County roads (UCRs) should be recognised as not being part of the ordinary roads network, and should be re-classified as Restricted Byways,[bold]&#xa0;[bold]and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]When a local authority declines to impose a traffic regulation order that is widely-supported by the public, there should be a right of appeal, either to an independent inspector, or a magistrate.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]September 2013
